    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    Applicant
    Represents an Applicant in the BTO system.
    ApplicantController
    Controller responsible for handling applicant-related actions, such as viewing and applying for projects, managing applications and enquiries.
    ApplicantMenu
    Represents the menu for an applicant to interact with BTO projects and manage their applications and enquiries.
    Application
    Represents a flat application submitted by an Applicant for a particular BTO project.
    ApplicationService
    Service class responsible for managing applications for BTO projects.
    ApplicationStatus
    Enum representing the various statuses that an application can have in the system.
    AuthenticationController
    Controller responsible for handling user authentication, including login and password change functionality.
    CLIView
    The CLIView class handles all the user interface interactions for the Command Line Interface (CLI) in the Build-To-Order (BTO) Management System.
    DataLoader
    This class provides methods to load data from CSV files and populate the corresponding objects for applicants, projects, officers, managers, applications, and enquiries in the system.
    DataSaver
    The DataSaver class provides static methods for saving project, application, and enquiry data to CSV files.
    Enquiry
    Represents an enquiry submitted by an Applicant regarding a BTO project.
    EnquiryController
    Controller for handling operations related to enquiries, including submission, modification, deletion, and replies.
    EnquiryMenu
    This menu handles the command-line interface for enquiry management.
    EnquiryService
    Service class responsible for managing enquiries related to BTO projects.
    FlatType
    The FlatType enum represents the different types of flats available in the BTO system.
    HDBManager
    Represents an HDB Manager in the BTO system.
    HDBOfficer
    Represents an HDB Officer in the BTO system.
    Main
    The Main class serves as the entry point for the application.
    MainMenu
    Represents the main menu of the BTO Management System.
    ManagerController
    Controller class responsible for managing BTO projects, officer registrations, and applications within the HDB Management System.
    ManagerMenu
    Represents the CLI menu interface for HDB Managers to manage BTO projects, officer registrations, applicant applications, enquiries, and reports.
    MaritalStatus
    Enumeration representing the marital status of a user.
    OfficerController
    OfficerController is responsible for handling operations related to officers and their interactions with projects, such as project registration, enquiry viewing, and application status updates.
    OfficerMenu
    The OfficerMenu class handles all CLI-based interactions for HDB Officers, including applicant-related features, project registration, managing enquiries, generating booking receipts, and booking flats for successful applicants.
    OfficerProjectRegistration
    Represents the registration of an officer for a specific BTO project.
    OfficerRegistrationStatus
    Enum representing the different statuses an officer's registration can have for a specific BTO project.
    Project
    The Project class represents a Build-To-Order (BTO) project in the system.
    ProjectController
    This controller class manages the operations related to BTO project listings, applications, and status management.
    ProjectRepository
    The ProjectRepository class is responsible for managing the list of projects in memory.
    ProjectSearchCriteria
    Represents the search criteria for filtering BTO project searches based on various factors such as neighbourhood, flat types, marital status, age range, and sorting preferences.
    ProjectService
    Service class responsible for handling operations related to BTO projects such as date conflict validation, project creation, deletion, searching, filtering, and sorting projects based on applicant criteria.
    RegistrationService
    Service class responsible for handling registration operations for HDB officers to apply for a BTO project.
    User
    Abstract base class representing a generic user in the BTO Management System.
    UserService
    Service class responsible for handling user-related operations such as authentication, password management, and retrieving user details based on different criteria.
    ValidationService
    A utility service class for validating common input data such as NRICs, passwords, and dates.
